+    /// to materialize *only* the requested order statistics. For a fixed, small set
+    /// of percentiles this is O(n) average time instead of O(n log n).
+    ///
+    /// `select_nth_unstable_by` partitions in place so that the element landing at
+    /// index `k` is exactly the `k`-th order statistic (every element before it is
+    /// `<=` it, every element after is `>=` it) — bit-identical to the value a full
+    /// sort would have placed there. Order statistics are well-defined on the
+    /// multiset, so ties produce identical reads regardless of partition order. We
+    /// capture each finalized order statistic *immediately* from the value the
+    /// select returns at the pivot, since a later select over the remaining suffix
+    /// may reshuffle that boundary slot.
